Detailed Description

Class Definition CFixedFrequencyTable for LLRP parameter FixedFrequencyTable.

  • Document Reference LLRP Specification Section 9.2.4.1.2.2

  • Document Reference LLRP Specification Section 16.2.3.4.1.2.2

This parameter carries the fixed frequency list that can be used by the Reader. The one-based position of a frequency in the list is defined as its ChannelIndex (i.e. the first frequency is referred to as ChannelIndex one).

void LLRP::CFixedFrequencyTable::assimilateSubParameters (  CErrorDetails *  pError  )  [virtual]
 

Assimilates the decoded sub-parameters into m_listAllSubParameters.

After fields are decoded, the CDecoder itself takes care of gathering the subparameters into m_listAllSubParameters. Once the end of the enclosing TLV (or message) is reached this assimilateSubParameters() function is called to create parameter refrences from the primary member variables.
